text.section:
Each unit of blood collected by a blood establishment for transfusion shall be affixed with the United States Food and Drug Administration required label which includes a donor identification number through which the following information can be obtained:
Date the blood was collected;
Name of blood establishment;
Nonidentifying code representing the name of the blood donor;
A blood establishment serial number for the blood;
The date of laboratory testing of the blood;
The name of the person and laboratory testing the blood;
The laboratory test results.
